Subject: Re: [T2] Swapping engines between a manual and automatic

On Mon, 14 Jul 2008, Troy Wical wrote:

> I am contemplating a swap between Buster (a '78 manual transmission)
> and Vandejo (a '74 automatic.)  The drive plate, and vacuum lines for
> the transmission immediately come to mind in regards to the swap, but
> I want to make sure there is something else that I may be missing.
> Both engines are 2.0 FI.

are you planning on putting the auto in the 78 or the manual in the 74
or both.

be aware there are quite a few major differences between an automatic
and a manual and swapping transmissions is a major project, would
require welding and fabricating. unless there is an important reason
for doing this I suspect you would be very sorry you started this
project.


Bob
78 Auto now (formerly a 71 manual)


